cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI

The paper deals with motion detection and video analysis, which are primarily computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves clustering and feature extraction, which are machine learning techniques, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with image processing and segmentation, which are related to information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of a novel motion descriptor, which could be considered an artificial intelligence technique, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category.
